se.js.jesdob
Class DobCollection

java.lang.Object
  se.js.jesdob.DobCollection
All Implemented Interfaces:
java.lang.Iterable<IDob>, IDobCollection
public class DobCollection
extends java.lang.Object
implements IDobCollection, java.lang.Iterable<IDob>

A DobCollection is a collection containing one or more IDobs (dynamic objects). It is possible to add objects to a collection, and to remove objects from a collection. It is possible to get IDobs from the collection, by index, or by searching a specific attribute and value. You can also filter the DobCollection by using a IDobQuery-object. This will make the IDob-object act more like a database. DobCollections can be exported to text as json-format, xml-format or dob-format. They can then be saved to files and read as dynamic objects when they are needed.
